author: The Columbus Dispatch
title: High-school football | MSL roundup: Bexley clinches title share on late TDs
text:
Bexley 31, Columbus Academy 20 
Sean Early scored the go-ahead touchdown with 3:06 left and Jack Nagle scored on an interception return 40 seconds later as Bexley (8-1, 5-0) clinched a share of the Mid-State League Ohio title by beating visiting Columbus Academy (4-5, 1-4). 

Jerome Buckner caught a 61-yard TD pass to put Academy ahead 20-17 in the fourth before Early scored on a 12-yard run. Two plays later, Nagle picked off a pass - Bexley’s fourh interception - and returned it 27 yards for the score. 

Micah Fliegel rushed for 100 yards on 13 carries for Bexley. 

West Jefferson 42, London 21 
Earl Braithwaite rushed for 183 yards and Conor Powell for 132, and West Jefferson (3-6, 1-4) scored 35 points in the second half to beat visiting London (5-4, 1-4) in the MSL Ohio. Michael Johnson had 209 yards rushing and two TDs for London. 

Whitehall 35, Madison Plains 12 
Earl Redman had 250 yards rushing and two touchdowns and host Whitehall (5-4, 4-2) cruised to an MSL Ohio victory over Madison Plains (4-5, 1-4). Cameron Near rushed for 115 yards and a touchdown and caught a TD pass for Madison Plains. 

Circleville 38, Amanda-Clearcreek 7 
Michael Camp passed for 260 yards and four touchdowns and rushed for another, and host Circleville (6-3, 3-3) cruised past visiting Amanda-Clearcreek (2-7, 1-5) in the MSL Buckeye. 

Teays Valley 31, Bloom-Carroll 7 
Teays Valley (7-2, 6-0) scored 24 fourth-quarter points to beat visiting Bloom-Carroll (5-4, 3-3) and clinch a share of the MSL Buckeye title for the second consecutive year. Colton Carroll burst through the Bulldogs defense for a 60-yard touchdown run to build a 17-7 lead early in the fourth and Tanner Oller added two more short TD runs to seal the win. 

Fairfield Union 28, Liberty Union 14 
Braden Heston scored on a 32-yard run in the fourth quarter to help Fairfield Union (4-5, 2-4) pull away from visiting Liberty Union (1-8, 0-6) in the MSL Buckeye. Heston rushed for 106 yards and two TDs. 

Hamilton Township 55, Logan Elm 34 
Jacob Long ran for four touchdowns and Hamilton Township (7-2, 5-1) gained 588 total yards in an MSL Buckeye win over host Logan Elm (6-3, 4-2). Long, who finished with 121 rushing yards, scored twice in the third quarter to help the Rangers build a 34-14 lead. Hamilton Township’s Trey Johnson ran for two touchdowns and Patrick Robinson threw for 272 yards and one score, an 18-yard strike to Mike Phimmasone, who had nine receptions. 

Worthington Christian 26, Fairfield Christian 13 
Alex Tucker completed 10 of 14 passes for 151 yards and two touchdowns to lead Worthington Christian (3-6, 2-3) over host Fairfield Christian (3-6, 2-3) in the MSL Cardinal. 

Harvest Prep 46, Fisher Catholic 9 
Daniel Bangura rumbled for 220 yards and scored four touchdowns to help Harvest Prep (7-2, 5-0) clinch at least a share of the MSL Cardinal Division with a win over Fisher Catholic (6-3, 5-1). Bangura, who only had 13 carries, scored on runs of 56, 7, 49 and 35 yards. Rodney Meyer threw three touchdown passes on six completions, and the Warriors defense had four interceptions, including three in the second quarter that resulted in touchdowns. 

Grandview 64, Grove City Christian 16 
Grandview (8-1) gained 502 total yards, including 318 rushing, in a victory over host Grove City Christian (0-9) in nonleague play. Hudson Jump scored four touchdowns -- runs of 4 and 10 yards, and receptions of 40 and 50 yards. Tavian Sim led the Eagles with 130 yards rushing.
